https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-parentheses/description/

Problem:
Give :([]) output:true
      (()[] output: false


Brute force approach:
  What i can see is just create a for loop and Stack. which will be spaceand time complex more

Good Approach:
-> Create a Stack
-> For every ( -> push to stack )  and  { -> } and [ -> ]
-> if not if it is ) then check if the st.pop== current charcter if not false 

eg: (([))
(   st-> )
(   st-> ))
[   st-> ))]
)  since st is not empty, st.pop()!=) ]!=) so false

CODE:
class Solution {
    public boolean isValid(String s) {
       Stack<Character>st=new Stack<>();
       for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        char ch=s.charAt(i);
        if(ch=='(')st.push(')');
            else if(ch=='{')st.push('}');
            else if(ch=='[')st.push(']');
            else if(st.isEmpty() || st.pop()!=ch)return false;
        }
        return st.isEmpty();
    }
}
            
